extends layout

block content
  .static-page
    .static-card
      span.static-eyebrow Privacy Policy
      h1 Privacy Policy
      p Effective Date: 26 April 2026

      .static-section
        h2 1. Introduction
        p Gaming Community respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and how we protect it when you use our website, create an account, post content, comment, rate posts, or interact with other users.

      .static-section
        h2 2. Information We Collect
        p We may collect information that you provide directly, including your username, email address, password, profile details, posts, comments, ratings, likes, reports, and any content you choose to submit.
        p We may also collect basic technical information such as browser type, device information, IP address, pages visited, and activity on the website to help keep the platform secure and improve performance.

      .static-section
        h2 3. How We Use Your Information
        p We use your information to create and manage your account, display your posts and comments, enable community features, improve the website, prevent abuse, investigate reports, and maintain the safety and security of the platform.

      .static-section
        h2 4. Public Content
        p Content you post on Gaming Community may be visible to other users and visitors. This includes your username, posts, comments, likes, ratings, and other public activity. Please do not share private or sensitive information in public areas of the website.

      .static-section
        h2 5. Cookies and Similar Technologies
        p We may use cookies or similar technologies to keep you logged in, remember preferences, improve user experience, and understand how the website is used. You can disable cookies in your browser settings, but some features may not work correctly.

      .static-section
        h2 6. Data Protection and Security
        p We take reasonable steps to protect your information from unauthorized access, loss, misuse, or alteration. However, no online platform can guarantee complete security. You are responsible for keeping your login details confidential.

      .static-section
        h2 7. Sharing of Information
        p We do not sell your personal information. We may share information only when necessary to operate the website, comply with legal obligations, enforce our rules, prevent fraud or abuse, or protect the rights and safety of users and the platform.

      .static-section
        h2 8. Third-Party Content and Links
        p Gaming Community may include links, images, videos, or embedded content from third-party websites. We are not responsible for the privacy practices, content, or policies of third-party services. Please review their policies before interacting with them.

      .static-section
        h2 9. Data Retention
        p We keep your information for as long as needed to provide the website, maintain records, prevent abuse, resolve disputes, and comply with legal requirements. Some public content may remain visible unless removed by you or by an administrator.

      .static-section
        h2 10. Account Deletion and Updates
        p You may request updates or deletion of your account information by contacting the website administrator. Some information may be retained where necessary for security, legal, or moderation purposes.

      .static-section
        h2 11. Children’s Privacy
        p Gaming Community is not intended for users who are too young to legally use online community services in their location. If we become aware that a child has provided personal information without appropriate permission, we may remove the account or related data.

      .static-section
        h2 12. Changes to This Policy
        p We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When changes are made, the updated policy will be posted on this page with a revised effective date.

      .static-section
        h2 13. Contact
        p For privacy questions, account requests, or data concerns, please contact the Gaming Community administrator.

      .static-actions
        a.static-btn(href="/posts") Browse Posts
        a.static-btn.secondary(href="/support") Contact Support